1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,196
In this video we cover two different ways of looking at math.

2
00:00:03,296 --> 00:00:06,438
On the one side, we have the mechanical world of syntax, and

3
00:00:06,538 --> 00:00:09,356
on the other we have the intuitive world of semantics.

4
00:00:09,466 --> 00:00:14,112
Each side has its own definition of truth. In the world of syntax, a

5
00:00:14,212 --> 00:00:18,439
statement is true if and only if we have a formal proof of it.

6
00:00:18,539 --> 00:00:23,394
This relation means that there is a proof of phi assuming all of Sigma.

7
00:00:23,466 --> 00:00:28,353
In the semantical side, truth is given by Tarski's definition of truth.

8
00:00:28,453 --> 00:00:32,215
Namely that something is true if and only if it is true

9
00:00:32,315 --> 00:00:36,640
in all models. We denote by this relation, that in all possible

10
00:00:36,740 --> 00:00:40,502
worlds where Sigma is satisfied, phi is also satisfied.

